  "title": "Cabinet-Style Kitchen Island with Wine Grid",
  "summary": "A full plywood-carcass kitchen island with face frames on all four sides, three drawers, two inset-hinge doors, and a diagonal X-braced wine bottle grid built into one bay.",
  "description": "The main carcass is built from wide-ripped plywood — a bottom, four sides/dividers splitting the interior into bays, and a plywood back — reinforced with back supports and closed in with face frames on the front, back, AND sides, since this island is meant to be seen and finished from every angle, not just the front. **Two plywood pieces set at a diagonal form an X inside one bay**, creating the wine bottle grid — this is the detail that separates this island from every other kitchen island in the catalog.\n\nThe base sits on four short 4x4 feet joined by 2x3 (or 1x3) rails, raising the whole carcass off the floor before the face frames and moulding go on. **All three face frame sections — side, back, and front — are explicitly recommended to be cut to fit** rather than trusted to the plan's numbers, since plywood thickness and assembly variance compound across a piece this size.\n\nThree drawers (sized to your actual slide clearance and opening) and two inset-hinge doors close out the storage, trimmed in thin wood moulding, with two corbels under the countertop overhang for support. **The countertop itself is made to fit** and isn't part of this cut list — source it separately once the carcass is finished and measured.",
